Joseph PARIZO, Plaintiff in Error, v. UNITED STATES of America, Defendant in Error. No. 318. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. May 5, 1930. Joseph A. McNamara and Guy M. Page, both of Burlington, Vt., for plaintiff in error. Harry B. Amey, U. S. Atty., of Burlington, Vt.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed.
